input: Anne is nice. Anne is smart. Erin is nice. Erin is quiet. Erin is white. Gary is nice. Gary is white. Harry is not nice. Harry is quiet. Harry is white. If something is nice then it is rough. If something is green then it is rough. If something is white and green then it is smart. If Anne is rough then Anne is green. If something is big then it is quiet. If something is nice and white then it is quiet. If something is green and smart then it is big. If something is quiet and rough then it is white. Question: Anne is not white.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Gary : obj
constant Harry : obj

constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Smart : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Nice Anne
axiom T2 : Smart Anne
axiom T3 : Nice Erin
axiom T4 : Quiet Erin
axiom T5 : White Erin
axiom T6 : Nice Gary
axiom T7 : White Gary
axiom T8 : ¬ Nice Harry
axiom T9 : Quiet Harry
axiom T10 : White Harry

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x → Rough x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Green x → Rough x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, White x ∧ Green x → Smart x
axiom R4 : Rough Anne → Green Anne
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Big x → Quiet x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ White x → Quiet x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Green x ∧ Smart x → Big x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Rough x → White x

theorem anne_is_not_white : ¬ White Anne :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Quiet Anne := R6 Anne ⟨T1, H⟩,
  have H2 : Rough Anne := R1 Anne T1,
  have H3 : White Anne := R8 Anne ⟨H1, H2⟩,
  contradiction,
end

-- The answer is True
